The paper deals with the problem of eye localisation in low-resolution images, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on gaze tracking, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of low-cost consumer-grade webcams for gaze tracking suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed algorithm involves machine learning techniques, which may also make it relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
